<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/68206905-luke-farnish"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1499417278i/68206905._UX100_CR0,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/68206905-luke-farnish">Luke Farnish</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">I started reading these in my early teens (I think I was 12?) and found them easy enough to understand. I&apos;d recommend around 12+ for most people as Cl<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">I started reading these in my early teens (I think I was 12?) and found them easy enough to understand. I'd recommend around 12+ for most people as Clarke's style can be a little fashioned at times but, to my memory of the stories I have so far read, there aren't any that are scary or particularly dark for the most part. <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
