<span id="freeTextContainer10392169851150821735"><b>Well you got &quot;2001&quot; wrong, and &quot;2010&quot;...and just about everything else.</b><br/><br/>In my late teens and early twenties, I adored Clarke&apos;s works and thought him a true visionary. Now that I reread some of his stuff, it turns out he was totally wrong about most of his predictions. No Moon-base. No manned expeditions to Jupiter/Mars(yet) or beyond. No visits by aliens (that we know of). And the racist and sexist views! Unsurprisingly, to me at least, I found his works now, to be outdated, inaccurate and boring</span>
  <span id="freeText10392169851150821735" style="display:none"><b>Well you got "2001" wrong, and "2010"...and just about everything else.</b><br /><br />In my late teens and early twenties, I adored Clarke's works and thought him a true visionary. Now that I reread some of his stuff, it turns out he was totally wrong about most of his predictions. No Moon-base. No manned expeditions to Jupiter/Mars(yet) or beyond. No visits by aliens (that we know of). And the racist and sexist views! Unsurprisingly, to me at least, I found his works now, to be outdated, inaccurate and boring, but there is still no doubting his writing talent.</span>
