<div id="review_3984406732" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3984406732" />
    <a title="Steve" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/49577120-steve"><img alt="Steve" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/m_50x66-82093808bca726cb3249a493fbd3bd0f.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3984406732?book_show_action=true">Sep 15, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Steve" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Steve" href="/user/show/49577120-steve">Steve</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3984406732" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16453568934180413995">When I started this book months ago my incorrect perception was that the author was not at the same level as Asimov. After reading all of these stories and experiencing their creativity, foresight, and entertainment, I learned how wrong I was. Besides the high quality of the content, I also give high marks to the chronological format of the book which is truly a gift to the reader who wants to experience the progression of the author&apos;s work through over half a century. I especially liked the sto</span>
  <span id="freeText16453568934180413995" style="display:none">When I started this book months ago my incorrect perception was that the author was not at the same level as Asimov. After reading all of these stories and experiencing their creativity, foresight, and entertainment, I learned how wrong I was. Besides the high quality of the content, I also give high marks to the chronological format of the book which is truly a gift to the reader who wants to experience the progression of the author's work through over half a century. I especially liked the stories from the decades of the Golden Age. The stories in the later years, when he was a world-renowned author, appear to be targeted at making statements. Overall this is a great book and a great way to immerse yourself in the work of a legendary SF author. </span>
  <a data-text-id="16453568934180413995" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


