<div id="review_2527578404" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2527578404" />
    <a title="Yevgen Antymyrov" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/7485119-yevgen-antymyrov"><img alt="Yevgen Antymyrov" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/m_50x66-82093808bca726cb3249a493fbd3bd0f.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2527578404?book_show_action=true">Jan 24, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Yevgen Antymyrov" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Yevgen Antymyrov" href="/user/show/7485119-yevgen-antymyrov">Yevgen Antymyrov</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2527578404" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10636610692916203254">When I was a kid, I loved reading sci-fi. Countless books and stories by Asimov, Sheckley, Harisson, Verne, and so on. But somehow Clarke was never available in our town library. While on vacation ten years ago, I read his trilogy, &quot;A Time Odyssey.&quot; No bad, I need to find more, I thought. And finally, I did it! It took me almost two months to finish this epic collection of 116 short stories. <br/><br/>Comparing to the other old-school science fiction, the science part in Clarke&apos;s books is mostly &apos;hard&apos;. S</span>
  <span id="freeText10636610692916203254" style="display:none">When I was a kid, I loved reading sci-fi. Countless books and stories by Asimov, Sheckley, Harisson, Verne, and so on. But somehow Clarke was never available in our town library. While on vacation ten years ago, I read his trilogy, "A Time Odyssey." No bad, I need to find more, I thought. And finally, I did it! It took me almost two months to finish this epic collection of 116 short stories. <br /><br />Comparing to the other old-school science fiction, the science part in Clarke's books is mostly 'hard'. So, no guys with blasters. Not sure how I would think of this at 13 yo.<br /><br />While I truly enjoyed most of the works, some of them were tragically boring. And a lot of stories had great premises, but failed to conclude with something more definite than "And the hero looked at the horizon deep in his thoughts." Maybe it's the short format that limits the number of pages. But yeah, a couple of missed opportunities, in my opinion.</span>
  <a data-text-id="10636610692916203254" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


